polyimide sensor. Both of these methods can reduce the errors to less\nthan 4% as compared to around 40% error of overestimation from raw values\nmeasured with the pristine sensor. Such results show that both the numerical\ncorrection to a pristine senor or an optimized sensor are capable of providing\nhighly accurate value of thermal conductivity for such materials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Oct 2019 04:34:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 Oct 2019 19:03:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-01"}
